<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-16T16:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-16T16:30:00-05:00" n="398" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/883a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VDH1" type="to">Van Dyke</persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-16T16:30:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1915, 4.30 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>130. American exporters tobacco and other non-contraband commodities
                                at present handicapped by action of Holland-America Line in refusing
                                to accept shipments. Articles of Oversea Trust appear to limit their
                                operations to contraband commodities. Can Oversea Trust accept such
                                non-contraband shipments? If not, will application be made to
                                enlarge its powers to enable it to do so, thus preventing
                                transshipment to Germany? If so, ascertain from Holland-America if
                                goods will be accepted consigned to Oversea Trust.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>